Interface IdVaultTokenHandler<T>

    public interface IdVaultTokenHandler<T>
extends UserTokenHandler<T>
    This service interface represents a provider that is able to process a token supplied to IdVault.getUserIdWithToken(Object, String) and retrieve a UserId implementation.

    • Method Detail

      • getUserId

        Optional<UserId> getUserId(T token,
                           String serverName,
                           IdVault contextIdVault)
        Processes the provided token object to look up a UserId representation.

        This method is potentially called when UserTokenHandler.canProcess(Object) returns true and should either:

        1. Return an Optional describing a user ID if found,
        2. Return an empty optional if the token was processable but no matching user exists (e.g. if this object represents one of many potential directories), or
        3. Throw an exception if the token was invalid or otherwise unprocessable.
        Parameters:
        token - the token to process
        serverName - the name of the server to look up on (may be ignored by implementations)
        contextIdVault - the IdVault instance calling the method
        Returns:
        an Optional describing a UserId, or an empty one if a matching user cannot be located
